CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 13, 1957, page B6, reads: "Learning Efficiency - Loblaws stresses efficiency, accurate service which is taught to potential cashiers like Miss Janice Finney and Mrs. Sarah Haywood at the store's downtown training school by Mrs. Donahue. The cashiers now at the new store have completed many hours of instruction."
TitMainTitle: Left to right: Janice Finney, Ruth Donahue, and Sarah Haywood, standing behind cash registers in check out area of Loblaws Grocery, with signs in foreground reading "All Shopping Bags Must be Opened for Cashier's Inspection"
